Just like 1984's "Jennifer Rush", Rush's second studio album "Movin'" was released in a wide wariety of versions throughout the world. The UK version was issued with entirely different artwork but had the same track listing as in the rest of Europe and Scandinavia. In the US and Canada and also in certain Eastern European countries like East Germany the albums had the same cover art as in Continental Europe but were released under the title "Jennifer Rush" and then also included different tracks from the 1985 version of Rush's debut album - and were consequently technically speaking compilations of material recorded and/or remixed over a period of some three years.
Included here are also the 12" mixes of the two main singles released from 'Movin'"/"Jennifer Rush"; "Destiny" and "If You're Gonna Lose My Love", The Spanish version of the latter and also the slightly different mix of "Hero Of A Fool" included on the North American versions of the album.
